CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 4, 1953 reads: "Red Cross Course Graduates - These nurse aides have completed their course in Home Nursing and Civil Defense and are prepared for attacks, man-made or natural. Mrs. Eunice W. Cook was the instructor... Mrs. Gertrude Underwood, Mrs. Ada Crosby, Mrs. Minnie Jackson, Mrs. Ada Hurt, Mrs. Ruth Travis, Mrs. Pearl Jackson, Mrs. Rebecca Thompson and Mrs. Beatrice Dunn-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: 2001.35.51036; Harris, Charles 'Teenie'; Group portrait of eight nurses, left to right; Gertrude Underwood, Ada Crosby, Minnie Jackson, Ada Hurt, Ruth Travis, Pearl Jackson, Rebecca Thompson and Beatrice Dunn, Eunice Cook in center, graduates from the Home Nursing and Civil Defense course, another version
